(633, 1, '2012-11-27 01:57:11', '2012-11-27 01:57:11', 'ValuVet''s primary mission is to improve value in our clients’ practices by enhancing the management of those practices and in addition, to facilitate the sale of practices and of partnerships.\r\nIn achieving our mission, we strive to:\r\noffer the most comprehensive service in all aspects of our consultancy\r\nimprove the quality of the lives of our clients, of your staff and the quality of the practices we visit\r\ngenerate an increased financial return for our clients\r\nWe work closely with you\r\nNo matter how large or small your veterinary practice, we understand the importance of working collaboratively. With our stability, geographic reach, maturity, depth of knowledge and experience, we are well placed to assist you.\r\n\r\nValuations\r\nThe basic premise of ValuVet is to provide a consistent, reliable and relevant practice valuation service and to provide clients with assistance in selling or buying practices. This service includes goodwill and equipment valuations, full practice appraisals for purpose of sale and our practice marketplace listing. In addition to this, we are also committed to providing services to our clients which will help them to achieve their business and financial goals in practice.\r\n\r\nPlease feel free to navigate our site to find more information on our products and services.', 'About ValuVet', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '625-revision-4', '', '', '2012-11-27 01:57:11', '2012-11-27 01:57:11', '', 625, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/625-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(634, 1, '2012-11-27 01:59:17', '2012-11-27 01:59:17', '<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n<a data-rel="prettyPhoto[consultants]" rel="prettyPhoto" title="Dr Tony Thelander" href="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_TONY_T.jpg"><span id="trans-border" class="trans-border-thumb overlay inset"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-654" width="150" height="150" alt="" src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_TONY_T-150x150.jpg"></span></a>\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_content title="Dr Tony Thelander <br/>BVSc, MBA, FAICD" class=""]\r\n<h6>ValuVet Principal</h6>\r\n[divider type="thin"]\r\n<p>Tony graduated from U of Q in 1970 and was principal of the Chermside Veterinary Hospital in Brisbane for 35 years. Tony completed an MBA in 1996 and attained his FAICD by exam the following year.</p>\r\n<p>As a life member of the AVA, Tony has served in executive positions at Branch and Division level as well as the ASAVA. He was an inspector for the ASAVA Hospital Accreditation Scheme for 10 years and a director of Provet for 24 years.</p>\r\n<p>Tony became a consultant for ValuVet in 2003 and became Principal and Director of ValuVet in 2007 after retiring from fulltime clinical practice.</p>\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n<a data-rel="prettyPhoto[consultants]" rel="prettyPhoto" title="Dr Hugh White" href="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_HUGH_W.jpg"><span id="trans-border" class="trans-border-thumb overlay inset"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-653" width="150" height="150" alt="" src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_HUGH_W-150x150.jpg"></span></a>\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class=" " rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_content title="Dr Hugh White <br/>BVSc (Hons), MVSc, MACVSc" class=""]\r\n<h6>ValuVet Consultant</h6><h6>Vet''s Practice Market Place co-ordinator</h6>\r\n[divider type="thin"]\r\n<p>Hugh is a graduate of the University of Sydney and was in a principal in private mixed veterinary practice for 33 years, in Kempsey and Armidale NSW. During that time he was involved for varying periods with the EVA, ACV and the Post Graduate Foundation.</p>\r\n<p>He is currently the Director of the Centre for Veterinary Education within the University of Sydney on a part-time basis and has been a consultant to ValuVet since November 2007.</p>\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n<a data-rel="prettyPhoto[consultants]" rel="prettyPhoto" title="Mr David Sharp" href="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_DAVID_S.jpg"><span id="trans-border" class="trans-border-thumb overlay inset"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-652" width="150" height="150" alt="" src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_DAVID_S-150x150.jpg"></span></a>\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class=" " rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_content title="Mr David Sharp <br/>B. Comm. NSW - Accounting & Business Finance" class=""]\r\n<h6>Chartered Accountant, Director - DFK Richard Hill</h6>\r\n[divider type="thin"]\r\n<p>David qualified as a Chartered Accountant in 1985. He worked with KPMG then PriceWaterhouseCoopers including working in Toronto, Canada for 7 years. In 1993 he founded Walker Sharp & Co which in 2005 became part of DFK Richard Hill. Initial training was in auditing many different sized companies from Multinationals to small private family companies in a wide range of industries. It was the subsequent experience in Business Workouts assisting financially troubled companies turn their fortunes around that provided a true education. David learned how a company could be changed to operate profitably and how to identify the real value in a business.</p>\r\n<p>In 1997 David started working with Jim Martin valuing veterinary practices in addition to his accounting & taxation practice. Since then David has assisted with the valuation of over 500 veterinary practices of all types in all States of Australia. His previous experience means that David brings to the valuations real business experience, providing a realistic view of the practice which ultimately will achieve the best result for both buyers and sellers. In addition, David is able to provide additional advice as part of the valuation process that can assist both buyers and sellers to maximize the benefit from the transaction both in terms of its tax effectiveness and improvements in profitability.</p>\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>', 'Our Consultants', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'our-consultants', '', '', '2012-11-28 14:16:15', '2012-11-28 14:16:15', '', 627, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/?page_id=634', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(635, 1, '2012-11-27 01:59:13', '2012-11-27 01:59:13', '\nDr Tony Thelander BVSc, MBA, FAICD (ValuVet Principal)\nDr Hugh White BVSc (Hons), MVSc, MACVS\nMr David Sharp CA (Charted Accountant)\n\nDr Tony Thelander BVSc, MBA, FAICD\nValuVet Principal\nTony graduated from U of Q in 1970 and was principal of the Chermside Veterinary Hospital in Brisbane for 35 years. Tony completed an MBA in 1996 and attained his FAICD by exam the following year.\n\nAs a life member of the AVA, Tony has served in executive positions at Branch and Division level as well as the ASAVA. He was an inspector for the ASAVA Hospital Accreditation Scheme for 10 years and a director of Provet for 24 years.\n\nTony became a consultant for ValuVet in 2003 and became Principal and Director of ValuVet in 2007 after retiring from fulltime clinical practice.\n\n[TOP]\n\nDr Hugh White BVSc (Hons), MVSc, MACVSc\nValuVet Consultant\nHugh is the Vet’s Practice Market Place co-ordinator and a ValuVet consultant. He is a graduate of the University of Sydney and was a principal in private mixed veterinary practice for 33 years, in Kempsey and Armidale NSW. During that time he was on the executive of the EVA for 7 years, was actively involved with the ACV and a member and President of the Council of the Post Graduate Foundation in Veterinary Science at the University of Sydney (now the CVE). Hugh is currently the part-time Director of the Centre for Veterinary Education and has been a consultant to ValuVet since November 2007.\n[TOP]\n\nMr David Sharp\nB. Comm. NSW – Accounting & Business FinanceChartered Accountant, Director – DFK Richard HillDavid qualified as a Chartered Accountant in 1985. He worked with KPMG then PriceWaterhouseCoopers including working in Toronto, Canada for 7 years. In 1993 he founded Walker Sharp & Co which in 2005 became part of DFK Richard Hill. Initial training was in auditing many different sized companies from Multinationals to small private family companies in a wide range of industries. It was the subsequent experience in Business Workouts assisting financially troubled companies turn their fortunes around that provided a true education. David learned how a company could be changed to operate profitably and how to identify the real value in a business.In 1997 David started working with Jim Martin valuing veterinary practices in addition to his accounting & taxation practice. Since then David has assisted with the valuation of over 500 veterinary practices of all types in all States of Australia. His previous experience means that David brings to the valuations real business experience, providing a realistic view of the practice which ultimately will achieve the best result for both buyers and sellers. In addition, David is able to provide additional advice as part of the valuation process that can assist both buyers and sellers to maximize the benefit from the transaction both in terms of its tax effectiveness and improvements in profitability.\n[TOP]\n', 'Our Consultants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-revision', '', '', '2012-11-27 01:59:13', '2012-11-27 01:59:13', '', 634, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/634-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
