e Vet''s Practice Market Place co-ordinator and a ValuVet consultant. He is a graduate of the University of Sydney and was a principal in private mixed veterinary practice for 33 years, in Kempsey and Armidale NSW. During that time he was on the executive of the EVA for 7 years, was actively involved with the ACV and a member and President of the Council of the Post Graduate Foundation in Veterinary Science at the University of Sydney (now the CVE).\r\n\r\nHugh is currently the part-time Director of the Centre for Veterinary Education and has been a consultant to ValuVet since November 2007.\r\n[/toggle_code]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n[prettyPhoto title="Mr David Sharp" link="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_DAVID_S.jpg" type="link" gallery="consultants" style="" class="" paragraph="true"]<img src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_DAVID_S-150x150.jpg" alt="" title="" width="150" height="150" class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-652" />[/prettyPhoto]\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class=" " rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_code title="Mr David Sharp" class=""]\r\nB. Comm. NSW – Accounting &amp; Business FinanceChartered Accountant, Director – DFK Richard Hill\r\nDavid qualified as a Chartered Accountant in 1985. He worked with KPMG then PriceWaterhouseCoopers including working in Toronto, Canada for 7 years. In 1993 he founded Walker Sharp &amp; Co which in 2005 became part of DFK Richard Hill. Initial training was in auditing many different sized companies from Multinationals to small private family companies in a wide range of industries. It was the subsequent experience in Business Workouts assisting financially troubled companies turn their fortunes around that provided a true education.\r\n\r\nDavid learned how a company could be changed to operate profitably and how to identify the real value in a business.In 1997 David started working with Jim Martin valuing veterinary practices in addition to his accounting &amp; taxation practice.Since then David has assisted with the valuation of over 500 veterinary practices of all types in all States of Australia. His previous experience means that David brings to the valuations real business experience, providing a realistic view of the practice which ultimately will achieve the best result for both buyers and sellers.\r\n\r\nIn addition, David is able to provide additional advice as part of the valuation process that can assist both buyers and sellers to maximize the benefit from the transaction both in terms of its tax effectiveness and improvements in profitability.\r\n[/toggle_code]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>', 'Our Consultants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-revision-72', '', '', '2012-11-27 11:37:14', '2012-11-27 11:37:14', '', 634, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/634-revision-72/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
