n a business.In 1997 David started working with Jim Martin valuing veterinary practices in addition to his accounting &amp; taxation practice.Since then David has assisted with the valuation of over 500 veterinary practices of all types in all States of Australia. His previous experience means that David brings to the valuations real business experience, providing a realistic view of the practice which ultimately will achieve the best result for both buyers and sellers.\r\n\r\nIn addition, David is able to provide additional advice as part of the valuation process that can assist both buyers and sellers to maximize the benefit from the transaction both in terms of its tax effectiveness and improvements in profitability.\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>', 'Our Consultants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-revision-74', '', '', '2012-11-27 11:49:49', '2012-11-27 11:49:49', '', 634, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/634-revision-74/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
