(789, 1, '2012-11-28 01:13:05', '2012-11-28 01:13:05', '<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n<a data-rel="prettyPhoto[consultants]" rel="prettyPhoto" title="Dr Tony Thelander" href="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_TONY_T.jpg"><span id="trans-border" class="trans-border-thumb overlay inset"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-654" width="150" height="150" alt="" src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_TONY_T-150x150.jpg"></span></a>\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_content title="Dr Tony Thelander <br/>BVSc, MBA, FAICD" class=""]\r\n<h6>ValuVet Principal</h6>\r\n[divider type="thin"]\r\n<p>Tony graduated from U of Q in 1970 and was principal of the Chermside Veterinary Hospital in Brisbane for 35 years. Tony completed an MBA in 1996 and attained his FAICD by exam the following year.</p>\r\n<p>As a life member of the AVA, Tony has served in executive positions at Branch and Division level as well as the ASAVA. He was an inspector for the ASAVA Hospital Accreditation Scheme for 10 years and a director of Provet for 24 years.</p>\r\n<p>Tony became a consultant for ValuVet in 2003 and became Principal and Director of ValuVet in 2007 after retiring from fulltime clinical practice.</p>\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n<a data-rel="prettyPhoto[consultants]" rel="prettyPhoto" title="Dr Hugh White" href="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_HUGH_W.jpg"><span id="trans-border" class="trans-border-thumb overlay inset"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-653" width="150" height="150" alt="" src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_HUGH_W-150x150.jpg"></span></a>\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class=" " rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_content title="Dr Hugh White <br/>BVSc (Hons), MVSc, MACVSc" class=""]\r\n<h6>ValuVet Consultant</h6><h6>Vet''s Practice Market Place co-ordinator</h6>\r\n[divider type="thin"]\r\n<p>Hugh is a graduate of the University of Sydney and was in a principal in private mixed veterinary practice for 33 years, in Kempsey and Armidale NSW. During that time he was involved for varying periods with the EVA, ACV and the Post Graduate Foundation.</p>\r\n<p>He is currently the Director of the Centre for Veterinary Education within the University of Sydney on a part-time basis and has been a consultant to ValuVet since November 2007.</p>\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>\r\n\r\n[row]\r\n[col type="1_3" class="" rem="false"]\r\n<a data-rel="prettyPhoto[consultants]" rel="prettyPhoto" title="Mr David Sharp" href="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_DAVID_S.jpg"><span id="trans-border" class="trans-border-thumb overlay inset"><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-652" width="150" height="150" alt="" src="http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/PROFILE_DAVID_S-150x150.jpg"></span></a>\r\n[/col]\r\n\r\n[col type="2_3" class=" " rem="false"]\r\n[toggle_content title="Mr David Sharp <br/>B. Comm. NSW - Accounting & Business Finance" class=""]\r\n<h6>Chartered Accountant, Director - DFK Richard Hill</h6>\r\n[divider type="thin"]\r\n<p>David qualified as a Chartered Accountant in 1985. He worked with KPMG then PriceWaterhouseCoopers including working in Toronto, Canada for 7 years. In 1993 he founded Walker Sharp & Co which in 2005 became part of DFK Richard Hill. Initial training was in auditing many different sized companies from Multinationals to small private family companies in a wide range of industries. It was the subsequent experience in Business Workouts assisting financially troubled companies turn their fortunes around that provided a true education. David learned how a company could be changed to operate profitably and how to identify the real value in a business.</p>\r\n<p>In 1997 David started working with Jim Martin valuing veterinary practices in addition to his accounting & taxation practice. Since then David has assisted with the valuation of over 500 veterinary practices of all types in all States of Australia. His previous experience means that David brings to the valuations real business experience, providing a realistic view of the practice which ultimately will achieve the best result for both buyers and sellers. In addition, David is able to provide additional advice as part of the valuation process that can assist both buyers and sellers to maximize the benefit from the transaction both in terms of its tax effectiveness and improvements in profitability.</p>\r\n[/toggle_content]\r\n[/col]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n<div class="line_plus"></div>', 'Our Consultants', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '634-revision-87', '', '', '2012-11-28 01:13:05', '2012-11-28 01:13:05', '', 634, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/634-revision-87/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
