(811, 1, '2012-11-27 01:38:40', '2012-11-27 01:38:40', 'Valuation – Practice Appraisals\r\nOne of the most important services we offer is the in-depth report which we are able to generate based on financial analysis, key performance indicators of the practice and on the staff interviews which we carry out during the practice visit. This report has proved invaluable to many principals as a sales aid for potential partners or purchasers, as an educational tool for staff development and as an aid in negotiating with finance companies with a view to re-financing.\r\n\r\nThe report targets strengths and weaknesses as well as highlighting areas of opportunity and concern. We are able to provide suggestions for improvement in many of these areas and this is often one of the major benefits derived from the valuation process.\r\n\r\nOur valuation system has been developed over many years by our experienced team of senior veterinarians who all have direct experience in practice ownership and management. The system is being refined constantly to reflect the changing nature of practice. As an overall package, we feel that we are providing one of the most comprehensive practice management services available and one by which our clients are able to benefit significantly.\r\n\r\nMore services…', 'Practice Appraisals', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '602-revision-2', '', '', '2012-11-27 01:38:40', '2012-11-27 01:38:40', '', 602, 'http://valuvet.com.au/_dev3/602-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
